    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="891"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d891">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 375.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that, in obedience to
                    your cabled instruction, I called on the 28th of April upon General Mirza
                    Mohammed Ali Khan, envoy extraordinary and minster plenipotentiary of the Shah
                    of Persia, at this court, and delivered to him a written notification of the
                    state of war existing between the United States of America and Spain and
                    requested him to communicate the same to his Government, which he engaged to
                    do.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
